		"description": "<p>You magically target the internal fluids of a creature, causing them to turn caustic and begin to melt the flesh from their bones. The target creature must make a Constitution saving throw versus your spell save DC. On a failure, the target takes 10d8+30 acid damage. The target may repeat the saving throw at the start of each of its turns. On a success, the spell ends. On each successive failure, the creature takes an additional 4d8 acid damage. If the creature fails its saving throw three times in a row, or if it is reduced to 0 hit points as a result of this spell, it dies as its flesh is completely dissolved and it collapses into a heap of bones.</p>",
